INSTALLATION and USAGE

On the system, ROS Groovy must be installed.
To then install and run this example, do the following steps:

1. set up the ROS environment
   > source /opt/ros/groovy/setup.sh

2. Create a workspace directory in a suitable place
   > mkdir ws && cd ws

3. Clone this git repository into the workspace's src directory 
   > git clone https://github.com/bmwcarit/ros_chatter.git src

4. Initialize the catkin workspace in the src directory
   > catkin_init_workspace src

5. Build and install the chatter example
   > catkin_make install

6. Setup chatter's shell environment
   > source ./install/setup.sh

7. Launch the chatter nodes
   > roslaunch chatter_receiver sender_receiver.launch

To run the test, follow step 1 to 4 and then:
   > catkin_make run_tests


